# Compiler-facing language reference

Compiler changes should start from the language contract. This reference
connects user-visible semantics to the design documents that constrain their
implementation.

## Language semantics authority

`docs/language-overview.md` is the canonical compiler-facing language
reference. It owns syntax, semantic invariants, edge cases and deferred
language surface.

## User-facing documentation

`docs/src/docs/**` contains explanations, examples and topic pages for language
users.

## Design boundaries

`docs/src/docs/codebase/design-scope/overview.bd` summarises accepted
mechanisms, constraints and intentionally excluded complexity.

## Memory access

`docs/src/docs/codebase/memory-management/access-and-aliasing/overview.bd`
covers shared reads, explicit copies and `~` access.

## Compiler ownership

`docs/src/docs/codebase/compiler-design/overview.bd` routes each language
feature to the stage or topic that owns its implementation.
